Solver & Helix72 Engine — Description

The Solver & Helix72 Engine is the interpretation layer of the system.
It converts raw metrics into structural meaning, using the Tri-Antagonist Matrix (4-role model) and Helix72 stability logic.

Core Function

Take metric outputs and determine:

who is driving load

who is resisting

how stable the system is

where failure begins

how it propagates through the body

This layer answers:
“What does the structure mean?”

TAM 4-Role Model (Canonical)

Agonist (Driver)
Side generating dominant load / directional push

Antagonist (Counterforce)
Side resisting or opposing the load

Bi-Antagonist (Stabilizer)
System maintaining balance, corridor integrity, and control

Tri-Antagonist (Anchor / Saboteur)
Node or zone where the system locks, compensates, or fails to preserve stability

