Chain Integrity Rules

CASCADE triggers (any one):

COM deviation ≥ threshold

spine curvature + lower-chain failure

two major lower-chain failures

persistent propagation overload

STRESS

stabilizer strain

rising asymmetry

moderate COM deviation

COMPENSATION

controlled deviation

stabilizers functioning

STABLE

minimal deviation

no major contradictions

Static vs Dynamic Separation

Two independent states:

STATIC STATE

posture structure

corridor alignment

persistent asymmetry

DYNAMIC STATE

motion behavior

COM drift

momentum

collapse progression

Example:

static: compensation

dynamic: stable

Origin Detection Engine

Finds true source of dysfunction, not visible symptom.

Each node is evaluated for:

local burden

transferred burden

compensated burden

persistence

Origin criteria:

strongest downstream propagation

highest persistence

weakest compensation success

earliest burden

highest local burden

Outputs

origin node

propagation path

terminal compensation zone

confidence level

Propagation Engine

Tracks how instability moves:

distal → proximal cascade

proximal → distal compensation

compensation loop

mixed propagation

Influences:

dynamic state

anchor zone

treatment targeting

Contradiction Detection

Detects invalid structural combinations:

Examples:

COM stable + cascade

stabilizer stable + COM unstable

low burden + severe anchor

When detected:

reduce certainty

soften conclusions

output:

mixed pattern

unresolved compensation

unstable but controlled

